NAPCO Security Technologies, Inc. (NASDAQ: NSSC) is the only pure-play security company that provides products and services in three verticals: 1.) Alarms & Connectivity; 2.) Locking; and 3.) Access Control and Surveillance.  The Company sells its products and services through a network of 10,000+ dealers across four business lines: NAPCO, Alarm Lock, Continental Access and Marks USA.  
Since the company’s inception in 1969, NAPCO has strived for continued innovation.  It has recently launched a slew of new products designed to provide recurring revenue streams and take advantage of the growing demand for connected home products and alarm systems that run on a 3G cellular network. 
With headquarters in Amityville, NY, NAPCO manufacturers its products at its Long Island facility and at its Company-owned factory in the Dominican Republic.
