ADT Alarm Service & Home Security System    
ADT Alarm monitoring Provides 24-Hour Protection
Every ADT monitoring center puts an extensive network, including system professionals, on call to help protect the people and things you care about most, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. All throughout the United States, ADT Security has a full-scale network of linked command centers strategically positioned to successfully offer continuous monitoring of your Protect Your Home-configured security system. The state-of-the-art technology integrated into this resilient, hyper-connected operation is only one of the many reasons more people choose ADT monitored home security over any other security monitoring company in America.
How ADT Alarm Monitoring Services Work
Following the ADT-monitored home security system installation process, when an alarm is triggered, a signal is sent from your home or business to one of the home security systems professionals at ADT. This ADT professional then alerts you to the possible security breach, along with the police, fire department or emergency personnel. This happens at the time the alarm goes off, Thanks to the ADT Monitoring System, all of this happens at the time the alarm goes off, allowing you the peace of mind that comes along with knowing you, your family and belongings are being protected.
ADT Delivers Comfort through Constant Connection
The ADT Security network is the most complete group of committed and interconnected Customer Monitoring Centers, supported by trained professionals and dynamic high-tech ADT Monitored home security equipment. Customers can also take advantage of ADT® Pulse, to give you the ability to manage and monitor your security from the palm of your hand.
Our comprehensive Protect Your Home installation process includes a system that utilizes ADT's monitoring services for your home security.
For more information on how you can get a home security system, head over to our ADT Monitored Home Security Equipment page.









